  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      With the development of population aging, the incidence of covert stroke and cognitive
      dysfunction gradually increased. Currently, there is still lack of prospective cohort study
      with large sample size on the relationship between perioperative covert stroke and
      postoperative cognitive dysfunction. The investigators will perform a prospective cohort
      study. The aim of the study is to determine whether there is an association between
      perioperative covert stroke and postoperative cognitive dysfunction in elderly patients
      undergoing noncardiac surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
